<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I usually pull to my pet. I pull from max range with STR debuff. I hit the pet attack button and keep running till im a safe distance. The pet pulls it off and i sit back and cast vitality drains to get em dead fast (Power regens faster than pet health). If 2 come, I mez one and help pet kill the first one then we kill the second. If 3 come, I mez the 2 adds, put the pet on passive then mez the one he was fighting and run with pet in tow. More than 3, I let the pet show me his devotion by letting him die for the cause <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> (while i sprint away).<P><BR>Quick cast is a life saver. When the nasty MOB gets too close, just hit it, then quickly hit the spell you want. Very seldom does it get interupted and often has bought me a new lease on life. Do not try to mez or root when your pet is hitting it. Use forgetful or a finishing nuke. Hope this helps some.<BR>Hjonvard
</FONT>
